Constant
I wrote a poem. Again. This poem I got during a Sunday worship. I just suddenly had the idea of the Lord being constant. He is the rock that we can stand on and can be assured that it will never move. You can rely on science, but the Word has always been there. You stand on trends, but you never know what the next fidget spinner could be. You could rely on relationships, but unless it is a relationship with God at the center (then you're standing on the rock anyways), you're not going to get anywhere. Some people might argue about the last one, but I'd want to provide my proof. My proof is in the 50% or more divorce rate, abortions, homosexual relationships, and other stuff. The idea of a mother-father-children family has gotten so perverted my the country taking God's ideas into our own control. But when you fall back on the Lord, it's all designed to be perfect. The Lord is constant. That's what this poem is about. Some people thought it sounded like a song, but I didn't write it to be put to music. I was in worship, so it may have had some influence.

You can check out this poem on my <a href="https://www.wattpad.com/story/138455392-poem-book">poem book project</a>.

People come and people go,
Relationships thrown to and fro.
But I stay constant, this you know.

Trends leave and come,
Societal pressure like a drum.
But constant satisfaction, it is Me it is from.

Life comes in like a storm,
Strife like a swarm.
But the constant rock, I am that norm.

It's you I love,
Everything, I am above.
You're the one I'm proud of,
I want to fall down like a dove.

I'm your rock,
I'm the dock.
In the storm,
I am your constant, never changing form.

"'Lord, help!' they cried in their trouble, and he saved them from their distress.
He calmed the storm to a whisper and stilled the waves.
What a blessing was that stillness as he brought them safely into harbor!
Let them praise the Lord for his great love and for the wonderful things he has done for them."
